sentence: James Dee Crowe (August 27, 1937 – December 24, 2021) was an American banjo player and bluegrass band leader.
James Dee Crowe (August 27, 1937 – December 24, 2021) was an American banjo player and bluegrass band leader.
He began playing the banjo early on and was offered a job with Jimmy Martin's Sunny Mountain Boys (or Sunnysiders), a backup group, in 1954.
